### ============================================
### Camel MCP Gateway — Requests de prueba
### ============================================
### Servidor: http://localhost:8080
### Endpoints:
###   POST /mcp  → JSON-RPC (Camel REST DSL)
###   GET  /mcp/sse → SSE Transport (Spring MVC)
###   POST /mcp/message?sessionId=... → Mensajes SSE
### ============================================
### 1. tools/list — Listar herramientas disponibles
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/list",
  "id": 1
}

### 2. tools/call — Listar objetos (objects-service)
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/call",
  "id": 2,
  "params": {
    "name": "objects-service_listObjects",
    "arguments": {}
  }
}

### 3. tools/call — Obtener objeto por ID
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/call",
  "id": 3,
  "params": {
    "name": "objects-service_getObjectById",
    "arguments": {
      "id": "1"
    }
  }
}

### 4. tools/call — Crear objeto
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/call",
  "id": 4,
  "params": {
    "name": "objects-service_createObject",
    "arguments": {
      "body": {
        "name": "Mi Objeto",
        "data": {
          "color": "rojo",
          "price": 42.5
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

### 5. tools/call — Eliminar objeto
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/call",
  "id": 5,
  "params": {
    "name": "objects-service_deleteObject",
    "arguments": {
      "id": "1"
    }
  }
}

### 6. tools/call — Listar Pokémon
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/call",
  "id": 6,
  "params": {
    "name": "pokemons_listPokemon",
    "arguments": {
      "limit": 5,
      "offset": 0
    }
  }
}

### 7. tools/call — Obtener Pokémon por nombre
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/call",
  "id": 7,
  "params": {
    "name": "pokemons_getPokemonByName",
    "arguments": {
      "name": "ditto"
    }
  }
}

### 8. tools/call — Obtener Pokémon por ID
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/call",
  "id": 8,
  "params": {
    "name": "pokemons_getPokemonById",
    "arguments": {
      "id": 132
    }
  }
}

### 9. Error: Método no soportado
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "resources/list",
  "id": 9
}

### 10. Error: Tool name inválido
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/call",
  "id": 10,
  "params": {
    "name": "servicio_inexistente",
    "arguments": {}
  }
}

### 11. Error: params sin name
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/call",
  "id": 11,
  "params": {
    "arguments": {}
  }
}

### ============================================
### SSE Transport
### ============================================
### 12. SSE — Establecer conexión
GET http://localhost:8080/mcp/sse
Accept: text/event-stream

### [Nota: La respuesta SSE devuelve un event: endpoint con
###  la URL /mcp/message?sessionId=<UUID>. Copia ese sessionId
###  para las siguientes requests.]

### 13. SSE — Enviar tools/list (reemplaza <sessionId>)
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp/message?sessionId=<sessionId>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/list",
  "id": 1
}

### 14. SSE — Enviar tools/call (reemplaza <sessionId>)
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp/message?sessionId=<sessionId>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/call",
  "id": 2,
  "params": {
    "name": "objects-service_listObjects",
    "arguments": {}
  }
}

### ============================================
### Health Actuator
### ============================================
### 15. Health check
GET http://localhost:8080/actuator/health
Accept: application/json
